WEBVTT

00:08.809 --> 00:10.144
[***]

00:53.854 --> 00:55.789
[***]

00:58.859 --> 01:00.628
SILAS:
I'll take this opportunity

01:00.661 --> 01:03.231
to pledge my loyalty
to the State.

01:05.499 --> 01:07.301
I stand before you,

01:07.335 --> 01:09.637
humbled by
the military traditions

01:09.670 --> 01:11.739
of our great planet, Terra.

01:13.674 --> 01:17.445
I dedicate this award
to my men.

01:17.478 --> 01:20.648
Two of whom gave
their lives on Rexor IV.

01:20.681 --> 01:23.817
I accept this
in their honor.

01:25.486 --> 01:27.121
Thank you.

01:27.155 --> 01:29.089
[APPLAUSE]

01:32.926 --> 01:34.795
Congratulations, colonel.
Thank you.

01:38.932 --> 01:40.334
Vera.
You must be proud.

01:40.368 --> 01:42.236
I am, naturally.

01:42.270 --> 01:44.538
Silas is all of the things
we aspire to be,

01:44.572 --> 01:46.740
a courageous
and unwavering leader.

01:46.774 --> 01:49.310
OLIN:
You're quite right.
But as they say,

01:49.343 --> 01:51.845
behind every successful man
is a great woman.

01:51.879 --> 01:54.348
In this case,
a formidable one.

01:54.382 --> 01:57.818
Your quick thinking
as the director of this mission

01:57.851 --> 01:59.420
saved us
many, many casualties.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.722
If you ask me,
this honor

02:01.755 --> 02:04.358
belongs to both of you.

02:04.392 --> 02:06.794
Thank you, general.

02:18.239 --> 02:20.474
I always knew
he was jealous.

02:21.675 --> 02:23.411
So despicable.

02:25.713 --> 02:27.948
He had to diminish me
in front of everyone.

02:27.981 --> 02:31.252
VERA:
I seriously doubt
he meant to diminish you.

02:31.285 --> 02:33.887
Tonight of all nights.

02:33.921 --> 02:35.889
When I receive
the honor of a lifetime.

02:35.923 --> 02:38.559
I thought
he was being kind.

02:38.592 --> 02:40.228
Kind?

02:40.261 --> 02:42.463
Yes, Silas.
To me.

02:42.496 --> 02:44.532
Anyway, I'm exhausted.
I'm going to bed.

02:46.900 --> 02:49.670
Do your ears
ring at night?

02:49.703 --> 02:50.804
I'm sorry?

02:50.838 --> 02:53.874
When you lie
down to sleep,

02:53.907 --> 02:56.377
do you see
your comrades' lives

02:56.410 --> 02:58.379
extinguished before
your very eyes?

02:58.412 --> 03:00.381
No, of course not.
Of course not.

03:00.414 --> 03:03.684
Did you go out looking
for your last two soldiers

03:03.717 --> 03:06.487
and half carry, half drag them
back to the ship?

03:06.520 --> 03:08.289
No, but that's hardly--

03:08.322 --> 03:10.224
What? The point?
I was going to say "fair."

03:10.258 --> 03:12.626
Fair. Because to
those families,

03:12.660 --> 03:14.295
that is exactly
the point.

03:14.328 --> 03:15.829
Silas--
No, no.

03:17.631 --> 03:21.902
Was that you who piloted
the ship back to Terra? Hm?

03:21.935 --> 03:24.738
Of course not.
Of course not.

03:24.772 --> 03:26.507
No, right?

03:26.540 --> 03:30.778
Because I would have
remembered you being there.

03:31.912 --> 03:33.781
Wouldn't I?

03:37.918 --> 03:39.887
[***]

03:41.855 --> 03:42.990
[DOOR SHUTS]

04:02.343 --> 04:03.477
[***]

04:06.013 --> 04:07.381
[BEEPS]

04:08.682 --> 04:10.851
[SOBS QUIETLY]

04:13.787 --> 04:16.757
[HEAVY BREATHING]

04:29.737 --> 04:32.606
[***]

04:38.946 --> 04:40.548
VERA:
You're up early.

04:40.581 --> 04:42.750
[NOTIFICATION BEEPING]

04:42.783 --> 04:44.985
[MACHINERY BEEPING,
WHIRRING]

04:49.490 --> 04:51.291
What is it?

04:53.861 --> 04:56.764
General Olin's called
an emergency meeting.

04:56.797 --> 04:58.866
With our current
atmospheric levels,

04:58.899 --> 05:00.701
we have a little
less than five months

05:00.734 --> 05:02.836
of air reserves.

05:02.870 --> 05:05.706
We need to return
to Rexor IV.

05:05.739 --> 05:07.975
We should be looking
to tap the resources

05:08.008 --> 05:09.777
of a planet
without inhabitants.

05:09.810 --> 05:12.045
The Rexorian people will
naturally try and defend--

05:12.079 --> 05:15.583
They're not people, Vera.

05:15.616 --> 05:17.451
They're a vicious species.

05:17.485 --> 05:19.720
They are protective of Hydran,
Cool and uncompromising.

05:19.753 --> 05:21.755
which indicates
they're intelligent beings.

05:21.789 --> 05:23.524
If we strip their planet,
we doom them

05:23.557 --> 05:25.393
to the same fate
we're facing now.

05:25.426 --> 05:27.695
Terra is dying.

05:27.728 --> 05:29.630
We strike now
while we still can.

05:29.663 --> 05:32.099
This will plunge us into war.
You of all people should--

05:32.132 --> 05:34.935
I have already
come to terms with that.

05:34.968 --> 05:37.971
If my services should end
on Rexor IV,

05:38.005 --> 05:41.041
then I know I will have given
everything to the State.

05:41.074 --> 05:43.010
To Terra.

05:44.912 --> 05:46.614
See you at the debrief.

05:46.647 --> 05:48.882
[***]

05:54.922 --> 05:57.491
[SIGHS]

05:57.525 --> 05:58.659
[***]

06:03.797 --> 06:05.733
OLIN:
We just recovered this
satellite transmission

06:05.766 --> 06:07.701
of our last mission
to Rexor IV.

06:13.641 --> 06:15.075
[BEEPS]

06:15.108 --> 06:17.077
We all know
how it ends.

06:17.110 --> 06:19.613
OLIN:
May they rest in peace.

06:28.689 --> 06:30.491
Based on this
morning's report,

06:30.524 --> 06:32.493
I'm moving up
the timeline.

06:33.827 --> 06:35.696
We need to get back
to Rexor IV.

06:35.729 --> 06:37.498
There's got to be
a better way.

06:37.531 --> 06:38.866
We should be negotiating.

06:38.899 --> 06:40.668
Finding ways we can
share the resources--

06:40.701 --> 06:42.703
This is insanity.

06:42.736 --> 06:46.740
Without Hydran,
we can't decontaminate our air.

06:46.774 --> 06:48.942
They have what we need.

06:48.976 --> 06:51.812
We secure it now,
before they can mobilize.

06:53.213 --> 06:55.983
Agreed.
Rexor IV is unstable,

06:56.016 --> 06:57.518
but they have more Hydran

06:57.551 --> 07:00.187
than the planets
we've mined so far.

07:00.220 --> 07:02.456
In an attempt
to avoid detection,

07:02.490 --> 07:06.494
I will authorize only
the MUSK OV-209,

07:06.527 --> 07:09.029
piloted by Colonel Herrick,
on a covert mission.

07:09.062 --> 07:10.598
You leave tomorrow.

07:10.631 --> 07:11.732
Yes, sir.

07:13.166 --> 07:15.102
[***]

07:29.550 --> 07:30.984
Headed to
the commissary?

07:31.018 --> 07:32.786
I'd like to
finish this report.

07:32.820 --> 07:34.722
Grab my usual?
Of course.

07:34.755 --> 07:35.723
[BEEP]

07:35.756 --> 07:37.057
I don't envy you

07:37.090 --> 07:39.059
having dinner with
your husband tonight.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.961
Like it could get
any worse.

07:40.994 --> 07:44.131
He never misses an opportunity
to undermine me.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.733
I'm so sorry.

07:48.669 --> 07:50.738
Yaro.

07:50.771 --> 07:52.806
Thanks for having my back.

07:55.308 --> 07:57.811
[***]

07:59.179 --> 08:01.248
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Going down.

08:04.752 --> 08:06.153
Pod level 92.

08:12.292 --> 08:14.695
[***]

08:14.728 --> 08:17.130
SILAS: Next, deposit--
Silas?

08:17.164 --> 08:18.899
--the manifest. Yes?

08:18.932 --> 08:20.100
Can I come in?

08:20.133 --> 08:21.969
I'm downloading.

08:26.674 --> 08:29.209
Deposit the manifest.

08:29.242 --> 08:30.944
Next.

08:38.285 --> 08:40.220
[HUMMING, BEEPS]

09:01.942 --> 09:03.744
[DOOR SLIDES OPEN]

09:03.777 --> 09:06.313
[***]

09:06.346 --> 09:07.781
[ELEVATOR CHIMES]

09:07.815 --> 09:09.249
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Going down.

09:09.282 --> 09:11.585
Deploying
breathing apparatus.

09:11.619 --> 09:13.553
[ALARM BEEPING]

09:27.234 --> 09:29.870
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Maze level, ground floor.

09:29.903 --> 09:31.839
[MUFFLED CHATTER]

09:33.774 --> 09:34.908
[HEAVY BREATHING]

10:26.059 --> 10:27.995
[***]

12:19.406 --> 12:21.341
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

12:28.448 --> 12:31.051
[MACHINERY POWERING DOWN]

12:32.585 --> 12:34.287
You were out late.

12:35.488 --> 12:37.858
The spacecraft
is on standby.

12:37.891 --> 12:39.860
I'm leaving.

12:39.893 --> 12:41.294
Already?

12:53.406 --> 12:55.342
[MACHINERY POWERING UP]
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

13:01.281 --> 13:04.451
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
11-A. Level 116.

13:08.321 --> 13:09.990
[***]

13:10.023 --> 13:11.925
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Going up.

13:15.128 --> 13:17.130
Message Silas.

13:18.866 --> 13:20.267
Silas, it's me.

13:20.300 --> 13:23.403
I'll be overseeing
the launch.

13:23.436 --> 13:25.038
Be careful out there.

13:29.109 --> 13:31.845
[NOTIFICATION BEEPING]

13:31.879 --> 13:33.180
Silas, it's me.

13:33.213 --> 13:35.883
I'll be overseeing
the launch.

13:41.088 --> 13:44.824
[***]

14:24.664 --> 14:26.599
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

14:35.242 --> 14:37.044
[ALARM BEEPING]

14:42.682 --> 14:45.018
[***]

14:45.052 --> 14:47.587
[ALARM WAILING,
SCREAMING]

14:47.620 --> 14:49.022
How long has
this been going on?

14:49.056 --> 14:52.159
Twenty minutes,
best we can tell.

14:52.192 --> 14:55.095
SILAS:
We're completely
surrounded.

14:55.128 --> 14:58.065
Restricted to defensive
positioning only.

14:58.098 --> 14:59.499
[VOICES DISTORTING]

14:59.532 --> 15:01.401
Request permission--

15:02.602 --> 15:04.304
Have you secured
the Hydran?

15:04.337 --> 15:05.672
Ship's at full capacity.

15:05.705 --> 15:07.407
The warhead's
in position.

15:07.440 --> 15:09.176
Will the ship
withstand the blast?

15:09.209 --> 15:10.978
If we switch to autopilot,

15:11.011 --> 15:13.246
and launch prior to detonation,
the ship might make it.

15:13.280 --> 15:15.482
And the crew?

15:15.515 --> 15:17.384
We're running out of ti--!

15:17.417 --> 15:18.718
We must get
the Hydran out.

15:18.751 --> 15:20.087
Activate the warhead.

15:22.722 --> 15:23.923
Do it, now!

15:29.196 --> 15:32.332
COMPUTERIZED VOICE:
Detonation in 10 seconds.

15:32.365 --> 15:34.001
Nine.

15:34.034 --> 15:35.702
Eight.

15:35.735 --> 15:37.137
Seven.

15:37.170 --> 15:38.571
Six.

15:38.605 --> 15:40.340
Five.

15:40.373 --> 15:42.075
Four.

15:42.109 --> 15:43.476
Three.

15:43.510 --> 15:44.611
Two.

15:44.644 --> 15:46.013
One.

15:46.046 --> 15:47.180
Detonation.
[EXPLOSION]

15:52.252 --> 15:54.054
[STATIC BUZZES]

16:00.360 --> 16:02.295
[HEAVY BREATHING]

16:22.515 --> 16:25.118
[***]

16:44.204 --> 16:45.772
MAN 1:
Sign off Helix 5.

16:45.805 --> 16:48.408
MAN 2:
Helix 5. Shutting down.

16:50.577 --> 16:52.112
YARO:
We weren't
expecting you.

16:54.714 --> 16:57.650
I'm so used to my life
revolving around his, I feel...

16:59.519 --> 17:01.354
...untethered.

17:02.455 --> 17:04.791
And guilty,
honestly.

17:04.824 --> 17:07.127
YARO:
You were against the mission
from the start.

17:07.160 --> 17:08.795
You can't blame yourself.

17:08.828 --> 17:10.597
I should have
fought harder.

17:10.630 --> 17:13.700
No, now's the time to fight.
Terra needs you more than ever.

17:13.733 --> 17:15.402
We need an aggressive
plan of action--

17:15.435 --> 17:17.270
I know.

17:18.871 --> 17:21.174
Silas would've wanted me
to get it together.

17:21.208 --> 17:23.310
Right.
Then do it for him.

17:25.212 --> 17:27.147
[***]

17:37.190 --> 17:38.425
[DOOR BEEPS]

18:16.463 --> 18:17.597
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

18:31.644 --> 18:33.580
[NOTIFICATION CHIMING]

18:37.317 --> 18:38.785
Yes?

18:38.818 --> 18:40.720
YORA:
The MUSK OV-209
was detected

18:40.753 --> 18:43.623
reentering our atmosphere
on autopilot.

18:43.656 --> 18:46.626
What?

18:46.659 --> 18:48.295
How?
I know.

18:48.328 --> 18:49.662
We can hardly
believe it.

18:49.696 --> 18:51.331
Carrying reserves
of Hydran.

18:52.399 --> 18:53.733
Was it unmanned?

18:53.766 --> 18:55.935
Sensors detect
life on board.

18:55.968 --> 18:57.404
Two lives, actually.

18:57.437 --> 18:59.639
Silas is one of them,

18:59.672 --> 19:02.642
but we don't know
what condition he's in.

19:02.675 --> 19:04.611
[***]

19:11.418 --> 19:14.254
Can I just say, your husband
is one remarkable man.

19:14.287 --> 19:15.388
VERA:
Where is he now?

19:15.422 --> 19:16.889
He's in the hospital,

19:16.923 --> 19:19.492
just completing
a thorough exam.

19:19.526 --> 19:21.628
Though I have to say,
he's uninjured.

19:21.661 --> 19:23.396
He even managed
a few words.

19:23.430 --> 19:24.831
What did he say?

19:24.864 --> 19:27.166
He wants
to come home.

19:35.742 --> 19:37.677
[SILAS GRUNTING]

19:46.253 --> 19:47.554
I'll call the doctor.

19:47.587 --> 19:48.721
No. No, no.

19:48.755 --> 19:51.324
Please. Please.

19:51.358 --> 19:52.592
Please.

20:00.900 --> 20:02.835
[GASPING]

20:08.007 --> 20:10.343
Everything's
going to be fine.

20:10.377 --> 20:12.312
[***]

20:13.646 --> 20:15.582
[PANTING]

20:20.353 --> 20:21.688
His breathing's
much easier

20:21.721 --> 20:22.955
but he's still
got heavy fevers.

20:27.394 --> 20:29.696
[DOOR BEEPS]

20:29.729 --> 20:31.764
General.
Go gently.

20:31.798 --> 20:33.800
He's been through one
hell of an ordeal.

20:33.833 --> 20:35.635
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:35.668 --> 20:37.437
OLIN:
Did the Rexorians attempt

20:37.470 --> 20:38.905
to force their way
on board?

20:38.938 --> 20:40.940
Well, they--

20:40.973 --> 20:43.710
They tried,
but the ship was secure.

20:45.077 --> 20:46.713
Anything else
you recall?

20:46.746 --> 20:50.049
Now, I-I do remember
pulling one of my men

20:50.082 --> 20:51.418
on board with me.

20:51.451 --> 20:55.021
Matthews.
You saved his life.

20:55.054 --> 20:58.358
Do you remember the specifics
of your journey home?

20:58.391 --> 21:02.329
I don't-- I don't know.
I-I must have...

21:02.362 --> 21:04.697
...blacked out or....

21:04.731 --> 21:06.299
That's enough for one day.

21:06.333 --> 21:09.402
My husband
needs his rest.

21:09.436 --> 21:12.004
Silas, you're positive
combat occurred

21:12.038 --> 21:14.006
entirely
outside the craft?

21:14.040 --> 21:16.776
Yes. We kept them out.

21:18.878 --> 21:20.513
Be well.
Thank you.

21:25.585 --> 21:26.719
[SIGHS]

21:38.731 --> 21:40.567
[MOANS]

21:43.570 --> 21:45.505
[***]

21:46.973 --> 21:48.541
Hm.

21:49.909 --> 21:53.546
I haven't seen you wear
your hair down

21:53.580 --> 21:57.517
like that in a long time.

21:59.786 --> 22:02.389
It's really nice.

22:04.156 --> 22:06.559
You're so beautiful.

22:37.690 --> 22:38.858
[WAVES CRASHING]

22:38.891 --> 22:40.026
[SEAGULLS SQUAWKING]

23:08.621 --> 23:10.089
SILAS:
It's no surprise

23:10.122 --> 23:12.492
how bad the food
is on Terra,

23:12.525 --> 23:15.662
but imagine a dehydrated
version of that.

23:17.129 --> 23:18.931
Hey.

23:18.965 --> 23:21.468
Looks like our patient's
feeling better.

23:21.501 --> 23:23.836
Let me look
at you.

23:27.139 --> 23:28.641
Mm.

23:32.612 --> 23:33.880
[LAUGHS]

23:33.913 --> 23:36.015
You know where
to find me.

23:36.048 --> 23:38.117
Thank you,
doctor.

23:41.187 --> 23:42.989
Have breakfast
with me.

23:44.557 --> 23:46.526
I'd love to,
but we're reviewing

23:46.559 --> 23:48.895
your ship's Titan Box
footage today.

23:50.162 --> 23:52.131
Oh, I-I thought it
was destroyed.

23:53.600 --> 23:55.034
Well, some of it
was salvageable.

23:55.067 --> 23:57.003
[***]

24:01.974 --> 24:03.910
[INDISTINCT YELLING]

24:10.216 --> 24:13.019
This is where Colonel Herrick
finds himself in trouble.

24:13.052 --> 24:15.121
He's dragging
Matthews.

24:17.056 --> 24:19.158
He's pursued
to the open hatch.

24:20.159 --> 24:21.594
He makes it inside...

24:24.096 --> 24:25.665
...just before....

24:29.836 --> 24:31.270
Colonel Herrick
assured us

24:31.303 --> 24:32.939
no part of battle
occurred on board.

24:32.972 --> 24:34.140
Yes, he did.

24:35.942 --> 24:37.209
Silas was in shock.

24:38.177 --> 24:39.746
Most of his men died,

24:39.779 --> 24:42.081
perhaps he doesn't
accurately recall

24:42.114 --> 24:43.249
this part
of the battle.

24:43.282 --> 24:44.851
Perhaps.

24:46.619 --> 24:50.089
We know two Rexorians
made it onboard that ship.

24:51.223 --> 24:52.825
What happened next...

24:54.060 --> 24:55.995
is what we need
to find out.

24:58.197 --> 25:00.900
[***]

25:19.686 --> 25:20.820
[DOOR BEEPS]

26:10.703 --> 26:12.639
[GASPING]

26:12.672 --> 26:14.240
Oh, I'm sorry.

26:14.273 --> 26:15.341
I'm sorry, I--

26:17.376 --> 26:18.978
I didn't hear you
come in.

26:19.011 --> 26:22.849
Yeah, I-I heard a noise
and then I...

26:22.882 --> 26:26.352
saw you like that,
and it scared me.

26:26.385 --> 26:27.887
Are you sure
you're okay?

26:27.920 --> 26:28.955
[SIGHS]

26:28.988 --> 26:30.823
I'm sorry.

26:31.958 --> 26:33.726
Silas.

26:33.760 --> 26:35.194
[***]

26:35.227 --> 26:37.029
What happened out there?

26:38.197 --> 26:39.699
I saw the footage.

26:39.732 --> 26:42.168
It was terrifying.

26:42.201 --> 26:45.004
You must have
feared the worst.

26:46.272 --> 26:48.340
And I was one
of the lucky ones.

27:15.367 --> 27:17.870
What's all this?

27:17.904 --> 27:19.038
You made breakfast?

27:19.071 --> 27:20.740
I did indeed.

27:20.773 --> 27:23.209
I don't remember
the last time--

27:26.713 --> 27:28.815
Where did you find them?

27:28.848 --> 27:31.984
Mm. A nondescript place
in the Maze.

27:33.820 --> 27:35.221
Go ahead.

27:41.160 --> 27:43.295
[LAUGHS]

27:43.329 --> 27:45.732
I know.

27:45.765 --> 27:47.800
It's incredible, huh?

27:47.834 --> 27:49.668
Oh, your tea's ready.

27:55.407 --> 27:57.343
SILAS:
I hope you like it.

28:11.123 --> 28:14.193
I know you don't want
to talk about it, but...

28:15.862 --> 28:19.098
You are entitled
to a level one psychologist.

28:20.366 --> 28:22.268
It can't hurt.

28:25.304 --> 28:26.873
Yeah. No, I...

28:28.007 --> 28:29.942
I think you're right.

28:31.911 --> 28:34.146
Okay.

28:34.180 --> 28:36.315
Homemade jam.

28:44.490 --> 28:47.193
You know, I just realized
I have an early debrief,

28:47.226 --> 28:49.061
so I should head in.

28:49.095 --> 28:51.197
Wait, wait, wait.

28:51.230 --> 28:53.966
Humor me.
Just try one bite.

28:54.000 --> 28:55.935
[***]

29:12.118 --> 29:13.953
That's really good.

29:29.368 --> 29:31.003
Out of curiosity,

29:31.037 --> 29:34.406
has Silas been talking about
coming back to work?

29:34.440 --> 29:36.876
Yes. Just this morning.

29:36.909 --> 29:38.144
Good.

29:38.177 --> 29:39.946
That'll be a relief,
right?

29:39.979 --> 29:41.213
[LAUGHS]

29:42.548 --> 29:44.183
You haven't noticed
anything unusual

29:44.216 --> 29:45.317
since his return?

29:45.351 --> 29:47.086
Nothing I'd
complain about.

29:47.119 --> 29:49.989
What does that mean?

29:50.022 --> 29:53.159
He's just different.

29:54.393 --> 29:55.461
Different how?

29:57.163 --> 29:59.531
I don't know, it's...

29:59.565 --> 30:01.901
hard to explain, really.

30:01.934 --> 30:03.069
It scares me a little.

30:05.571 --> 30:07.373
You think the Rexorians
got to him?

30:08.440 --> 30:09.608
Of course not.

30:09.641 --> 30:11.177
Vera, listen to me.

30:11.210 --> 30:14.847
These Rexorians
are extremely dangerous.

30:14.881 --> 30:16.415
You need to
keep your guard up.

30:16.448 --> 30:18.084
Be vigilant.

30:20.519 --> 30:22.421
[SIGHS]

30:29.028 --> 30:32.264
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

30:32.298 --> 30:33.432
[***]

30:41.540 --> 30:42.508
Hi.

30:44.443 --> 30:45.377
Hi.

30:46.578 --> 30:48.981
Your dinner's cold.

30:49.015 --> 30:51.550
I thought you would

30:51.583 --> 30:54.286
let me know if you were
gonna be late.

30:54.320 --> 30:56.622
I got held up at the office.
You had to assume--

30:56.655 --> 30:59.491
No, it's--
It's not important.

31:03.162 --> 31:05.297
You must be starving.

31:05.331 --> 31:06.966
I'll warm up
your plate.

31:06.999 --> 31:07.934
Thank you.

31:26.452 --> 31:29.255
I'm going to change out
of these clothes.

31:46.705 --> 31:48.040
[***]

32:03.489 --> 32:05.491
[***]

33:32.411 --> 33:34.446
What's that look?

33:38.550 --> 33:42.554
I can't remember you ever
touching me like that.

33:59.838 --> 34:01.607
[DOOR SLAMS OPEN]

34:01.640 --> 34:03.575
[***]

34:05.211 --> 34:07.146
[SILAS GRUNTING]

34:10.549 --> 34:11.750
Stop!

34:11.783 --> 34:13.152
[SCREAMS]

34:13.185 --> 34:15.421
AGENT:
Stop! I'll shoot!

34:15.454 --> 34:16.755
Don't!

34:16.788 --> 34:18.357
Leave my wife--!
AGENT: Don't move!

34:18.390 --> 34:19.825
My husband's
a level one colonel!

34:19.858 --> 34:22.628
AGENT:
Colonel Herrick,
you're under arrest.

34:22.661 --> 34:25.164
All powers granted
by the State are suspended

34:25.197 --> 34:27.266
until further notice.

34:32.438 --> 34:33.739
What the hell is going on?

34:33.772 --> 34:35.407
Bursting into
my home like that.

34:35.441 --> 34:36.708
General Olin's orders.

34:36.742 --> 34:37.709
Where is he?

34:37.743 --> 34:38.744
In the conference room.

34:38.777 --> 34:39.845
Prepare yourself.

34:39.878 --> 34:41.347
There's been
a development.

34:41.380 --> 34:43.249
INTERROGATOR:
Private Matthews

34:43.282 --> 34:45.317
you've been talking
in your sleep.

34:45.351 --> 34:48.554
Your partner caught some
of it the other night.

34:48.587 --> 34:50.522
[SCREECHING, CROAKING]

34:55.694 --> 34:57.163
MATTHEWS:
I mean, how bizarre.

34:57.196 --> 34:58.464
INTERROGATOR:
Not really.

34:58.497 --> 34:59.765
It's a plea
to bring your comrades

34:59.798 --> 35:01.433
back from the dead.

35:01.467 --> 35:03.469
In Rexorian.

35:03.502 --> 35:04.736
MATTHEWS:
You're lying!

35:04.770 --> 35:07.506
[GROWLING, ROARING]

35:12.878 --> 35:14.546
He's a Metamorph.

35:14.580 --> 35:16.615
Inhabiting one of our men.

35:16.648 --> 35:18.817
We've never seen
a Metamorph from Rexor.

35:18.850 --> 35:23.422
We very clearly saw two
Rexorians infiltrate the Musk.

35:23.455 --> 35:26.192
It explains how
they survived the blast.

35:26.225 --> 35:28.160
[***]

35:31.697 --> 35:34.733
This being is not
your husband.

35:38.237 --> 35:41.440
I'm gonna ask you
one more time,

35:41.473 --> 35:44.443
what is your name
and rank?

35:44.476 --> 35:46.912
[TASER BUZZES]
[SILAS GRUNTS]

35:46.945 --> 35:48.947
Silas Herrick.

35:48.980 --> 35:50.516
Level one Army Colonel.

35:50.549 --> 35:55.321
No, your Rexorian
name and rank.

35:55.354 --> 35:57.789
SILAS:
You're fishing.

35:59.491 --> 36:02.694
Trying to induce
a confession.

36:02.728 --> 36:04.230
It's ridiculous.

36:04.263 --> 36:05.797
INTERROGATOR:
You must be tired.

36:05.831 --> 36:07.433
Tell me the truth,

36:07.466 --> 36:09.668
and I will let
you rest comfortably.

36:09.701 --> 36:12.304
What's your name?

36:15.574 --> 36:17.976
Silas Herrick.

36:18.009 --> 36:20.912
INTERROGATOR:
How did you meet
your wife?

36:23.014 --> 36:25.617
SILAS:
We were paired by
the State

36:25.651 --> 36:29.355
after the Procreation Mandate
went into effect.

36:29.388 --> 36:33.359
She walked into our

36:33.392 --> 36:37.763
arranged meeting room
with such confidence.

36:37.796 --> 36:41.700
But there was such...

36:43.001 --> 36:45.837
tenderness
behind her eyes.

36:47.539 --> 36:50.809
Huh. That's what I remember,
the tenderness.

36:52.278 --> 36:54.012
INTERROGATOR:
Impressive recall,

36:54.045 --> 36:55.881
but it won't save you,

36:55.914 --> 36:58.617
because your fellow soldier
gave you up.

36:58.650 --> 37:00.586
[***]

37:06.325 --> 37:07.893
What?

37:15.000 --> 37:16.502
Because he's
a level one,

37:16.535 --> 37:18.504
we can't terminate
without a trial.

37:18.537 --> 37:19.738
We will be counting

37:19.771 --> 37:21.039
on your testimony.

37:21.072 --> 37:23.241
Of course.

37:24.710 --> 37:26.945
My loyalty is to
the State.

37:26.978 --> 37:28.814
[TASER BUZZES]
[SILAS GROANS]

37:30.882 --> 37:32.818
[***]

37:36.488 --> 37:38.424
[***]

37:52.838 --> 37:54.773
JUDGE:
Won't you begin, counsel?

37:54.806 --> 37:57.008
STATE'S ADVOCATE:
Certainly.

37:57.042 --> 38:00.712
This is not
Colonel Silas Herrick,

38:00.746 --> 38:04.683
but in fact a Metamorph
from the planet Rexor IV.

38:04.716 --> 38:06.718
The State calls
General Olin.

38:15.861 --> 38:18.430
What do you know about
Metamorphs?

38:19.831 --> 38:21.933
They're ruthless,

38:21.967 --> 38:25.671
conniving beings with
no empathy or moral code.

38:25.704 --> 38:27.806
As we have witnessed
with the infecting

38:27.839 --> 38:31.643
of Private Matthews,
they have no remorse

38:31.677 --> 38:33.512
for the lives
they've taken.

38:35.514 --> 38:36.982
We can only imagine

38:37.015 --> 38:39.651
what they intend
here on Terra.

38:39.685 --> 38:42.754
A Metamorph inhabits a human
being completely,

38:42.788 --> 38:44.990
melding with their DNA.

38:45.023 --> 38:47.926
They acquire their
host's mind and memories.

38:47.959 --> 38:50.962
In your esteemed
professional opinion,

38:51.930 --> 38:53.399
does Silas Herrick

38:53.432 --> 38:55.667
sit before us?

39:01.707 --> 39:03.409
No.

39:03.442 --> 39:05.544
[CROWD WHISPERING]

39:05.577 --> 39:09.415
STATE'S ADVOCATE:
Director Herrick,
please take the stand.

39:13.118 --> 39:15.854
[***]

39:24.663 --> 39:26.732
According to a colleague,

39:26.765 --> 39:28.967
you had doubts about
your husband's behavior

39:29.000 --> 39:30.436
after his return
from Rexor.

39:30.469 --> 39:31.703
Why is that?

39:31.737 --> 39:34.039
He was...

39:34.072 --> 39:36.708
tense before he left.

39:36.742 --> 39:38.043
Disconnected.

39:39.745 --> 39:42.448
His demeanor changed
when he came back.

39:42.481 --> 39:45.417
Did it ever occur to you
he could be a Rexorian?

39:45.451 --> 39:46.818
No.

39:46.852 --> 39:48.654
Were you then shocked
when he was arrested?

39:48.687 --> 39:50.021
Very.

39:52.658 --> 39:54.993
But...

39:55.026 --> 39:56.695
in retrospect,

39:56.728 --> 39:59.431
I can understand it.

39:59.465 --> 40:01.733
Terra is in a state
of emergency.

40:03.101 --> 40:04.803
And many of us
have difficulties

40:04.836 --> 40:07.673
keeping our fears
in check.

40:07.706 --> 40:09.641
Do you now believe
that the man

40:09.675 --> 40:12.444
sitting right over there
is your husband?

40:35.801 --> 40:37.168
Yes, I do.

40:37.202 --> 40:39.137
[CROWD MURMURING]

40:45.511 --> 40:46.878
[GAVEL TAPS]

40:46.912 --> 40:48.914
Any further questions,
counsel?

40:48.947 --> 40:50.549
Ah, no.

40:50.582 --> 40:52.751
JUDGE:
You may step down.

40:55.020 --> 40:58.156
Your Honor, I'd like a moment
to confer with a State official.

41:07.966 --> 41:10.235
The State calls
Yaro Peterson.

41:19.244 --> 41:21.513
How long have you known
Director Vera Herrick?

41:22.981 --> 41:24.750
We've worked together
for over a decade.

41:24.783 --> 41:26.818
I consider her a friend.

41:26.852 --> 41:30.956
How did she seem after the
colonel's return from Rexor IV?

41:30.989 --> 41:33.091
Distracted.

41:33.124 --> 41:34.560
Troubled, I'd say.

41:34.593 --> 41:35.861
During this period of time,

41:35.894 --> 41:38.029
did Vera tell you
she had suspicions?

41:38.063 --> 41:39.865
Yes.

41:39.898 --> 41:42.100
She confided
he was a different man.

41:42.133 --> 41:43.535
Different, how?

41:45.070 --> 41:47.573
She was evasive.

41:47.606 --> 41:49.641
It seemed
she was protecting him.

41:49.675 --> 41:51.543
STATE'S ADVOCATE:
You're suggesting

41:51.577 --> 41:53.211
that Vera Herrick
knew all along

41:53.244 --> 41:55.180
that the defendant
is a Metamorph?

41:57.883 --> 41:59.284
Yes.

41:59.317 --> 42:02.153
I believe she has knowingly
and willingly been

42:02.187 --> 42:05.657
harboring a Metamorph from Rexor
since the day he returned.

42:05.691 --> 42:07.793
[CROWD MURMURING]

42:07.826 --> 42:09.995
STATE'S ADVOCATE:
Ms. Peterson,
what you're saying

42:10.028 --> 42:12.964
is tantamount to treason.

42:12.998 --> 42:14.132
[GAVEL TAPS]

42:19.070 --> 42:20.238
Your Honor.

42:21.272 --> 42:23.141
I would like to testify.

42:45.731 --> 42:47.699
These are...

42:48.700 --> 42:50.101
challenging times.

42:52.704 --> 42:54.339
But I am not your enemy.

42:56.041 --> 42:58.944
I am Colonel Silas Herrick.

43:00.345 --> 43:04.115
And yes,
perhaps I am different now.

43:07.018 --> 43:09.755
Clearly, the State
has something else in mind.

43:09.788 --> 43:11.289
You have formed
your own conclusions,

43:11.322 --> 43:13.759
and in your rush
to judgment

43:13.792 --> 43:15.961
you're willing
to ensnare and endanger

43:15.994 --> 43:17.996
the lives of
innocent people, mine...

43:20.799 --> 43:22.167
And my wife.

43:26.905 --> 43:30.041
If it's a confession
that you need, you'll have it.

43:30.075 --> 43:31.242
But on one condition.

43:33.111 --> 43:37.115
Vera Herrick is exonerated
from any and all wrong-doing.

43:39.050 --> 43:41.920
If you agree to those
conditions then...

43:44.289 --> 43:46.391
then I am a Rexorian.

43:46.424 --> 43:49.294
[CROWD MURMURING]

43:49.327 --> 43:51.830
I have nothing further to say.

43:52.998 --> 43:55.734
Silas Herrick
is not human.

43:56.768 --> 43:58.303
We urge the State

43:58.336 --> 44:01.039
to accept
the defendant's terms.

44:01.072 --> 44:02.207
JUDGE:
We do.

44:02.240 --> 44:03.374
[GAVEL BANGS]

44:03.408 --> 44:05.076
Take him away.

44:08.046 --> 44:10.782
Your honor.
Permission to address the court.

44:12.083 --> 44:13.752
Permission granted.

44:24.495 --> 44:27.899
General Olin
clearly stated

44:27.933 --> 44:31.102
Rexorians lack
a moral code.

44:31.136 --> 44:33.438
They show no empathy.

44:33.471 --> 44:35.707
Does the court agree that
both these statements

44:35.741 --> 44:37.843
made under oath are true?

44:37.876 --> 44:39.410
JUDGE:
Yes.

44:39.444 --> 44:44.015
Then, Your Honor, the defendant
cannot be a Rexorian.

44:44.049 --> 44:48.954
A Metamorph would never choose
his own demise over another's.

44:48.987 --> 44:50.722
And yet...

44:52.190 --> 44:54.392
you have all
just witnessed him

44:54.425 --> 44:57.228
forfeit his life for mine.

44:57.262 --> 45:01.733
He has willingly given up
his hard won legacy,

45:01.767 --> 45:05.036
allowing all of you to
think the worst of him,

45:05.070 --> 45:08.439
even sentence him
to death,

45:08.473 --> 45:11.309
rather than see
harm come to me.

45:13.411 --> 45:15.313
Is he human?

45:17.248 --> 45:19.918
If sacrifice,

45:19.951 --> 45:21.853
kindness,

45:21.887 --> 45:24.255
and love

45:24.289 --> 45:28.193
is not the ultimate test
of what makes someone human...

45:31.997 --> 45:37.969
then what is?

45:38.003 --> 45:40.738
[***]

45:58.489 --> 46:00.125
Vera?

46:02.360 --> 46:04.195
Are you all right?

46:18.409 --> 46:21.212
Don't you think it's time
you told me your real name?

46:34.926 --> 46:38.063
I'm afraid you wouldn't
be able to pronounce it.

46:43.468 --> 46:46.437
The sounds can't be formed.

46:47.605 --> 46:49.507
In that case...

46:51.877 --> 46:54.512
I'd still like
to call you Silas,

46:55.947 --> 46:57.415
if you don't mind.

47:04.089 --> 47:09.460
[BOTH EXHALE]

47:09.494 --> 47:12.163
["WONDERWALL" COVER
BY CAT POWER PLAYING]

47:15.066 --> 47:18.303
* Today is gonna be the day *

47:18.336 --> 47:24.042
* That they're gonna throw
It back to you *

47:24.075 --> 47:28.546
* Right now, you should have
Somehow realized *

47:28.579 --> 47:32.450
* What you gotta do *

47:32.483 --> 47:36.988
* And I don't believe
That anybody *

47:37.022 --> 47:40.458
* Feels the way I do *

47:40.491 --> 47:43.294
* About you now *

47:51.236 --> 47:54.605
* Backbeat, the word
Is on the street *

47:54.639 --> 47:58.209
* That the fire in
Your heart is out *

48:00.245 --> 48:03.581
* I'm sure you've heard
It all before *

48:03.614 --> 48:08.686
* But you never
Really had a doubt *

48:08.719 --> 48:12.991
* I don't believe
That anybody *

48:13.024 --> 48:16.227
* Feels the way I do *

48:16.261 --> 48:18.964
* About you now *
